title: Rostov-on-Don, Russia, Home to Key Military Base, Is Rocked by Drone Strikes
description: Ukraine never acknowledges strikes on Russian soil, but the incursions are happening with increasing frequency.

title: Friday Briefing: A G20 Preview
description: Also, how Mattel made “Barbie” a hit.

title: Researchers Identify Jews Aided by Catholics in Nazi Era as Pope Was Silent
description: The names were found in documents recently studied by the Vatican, but historians say they don’t change the fundamental understanding of the church’s actions during the war.

title: Top French Court Upholds Abaya Ban in Schools
description: Critics of a new decree barring public school students from wearing abayas — loosefitting robes worn by some Muslim women — had filed an emergency petition calling the measure discriminatory.

title: Bill Gates, Marie Kondo and World Bank Head Will Speak at Times Climate Event
description: Sign up to watch the livestream and connect with online attendees about solutions to the climate crisis on Thursday, Sept. 21.

title: India’s Preparations for G20 Summit Must Also Account for Monkeys
description: For India, monkeys are a minor problem, compared with poverty and pollution, but the government doesn’t want them stealing the spotlight when world leaders arrive.

title: Spain’s Female Soccer Players Strike Over Wage Dispute
description: The season was scheduled to begin on Friday, but the players refused to play after talks with the league brought no agreement. The dispute comes amid a debate over sexism and soccer in Spain.

title: Teams in Turkey Try to Rescue Sick American From Underground Cave
description: Mark Dickey, an American cave specialist, fell ill and was unable to climb out on his own. Medical teams say his condition is improving.

title: Extreme Weather in Greece Traps Residents and Submerges Villages
description: Greek military forces were called in to assist the rescue efforts. At least four people in Greece and at least nine in neighboring Turkey have died this week amid torrential rains and flooding.

title: Palestinian Leader’s Antisemitic Comments Cause Uproar
description: Mahmoud Abbas, the president of the Palestinian Authority, said in August that European Jews were persecuted for what he said were their predatory lending practices, not their religion.

title: U.S. Seized Iranian Oil Over Smuggling Incident That Escalated Tensions in Gulf
description: The apprehension of the ship, the Suez Rajan, came after a group opposed to Iran raised accusations of sanctions violations last year.

title: Gabon Military Says Deposed President Is Free to Leave the Country
description: Before Ali Bongo Ondimba was ousted in late August, he and his family had ruled over the oil-rich, central African state for more than half a century.

title: Russia-Ukraine War: Southern Russian City Rocked By Explosions
description: Russian officials said air defenses shot down two drones over Rostov-on-Don, home to Russia’s southern military headquarters. Ukraine did not immediately comment.

title: Can India’s Global Ambitions Survive Its Deepening Chasms at Home?
description: India’s hosting of the G20 summit this weekend will put its growing power on display. But its leader’s divisive religious politics threatens its rise.

title: Thursday Briefing
description: Mexico decriminalizes abortion.

title: Bali Elevator Plunges Into Ravine, Killing 5
description: The crash in Bali, an Indonesian island where tourism drives the economy, is under investigation. The victims were part of the resort’s housekeeping staff.

title: ‘They Blew Our Lives Up’: South Sudanese Flee War in Sudan
description: Hundreds of thousands fled a grisly civil conflict years ago to settle in Sudan, to the north. With war now raging there, they are streaming home to a country ill-prepared to take them back.

title: Ukrainians Embrace Cluster Munitions, but Are They Helping?
description: The weapons, banned by most countries over human rights concerns, are ‘not a magic wand,’ but some Ukrainian troops say they are making a difference in fighting Russian forces.

title: Russian Missile Strike Leaves Scene of Carnage at Market in Ukraine
description: A Russian missile strike in Kostyantynivka that killed at least 17 and injured more than 30 others was one of the deadliest in months.

title: Mexico’s Next President Will Be a Woman
description: Mexico will elect its first woman as president next year after the governing party chose Claudia Sheinbaum to square off against the opposition’s candidate, Xóchitl Gálvez.
